@NODE MAIN
@TITLE "MMUPLAYSMP(1)ĀmanualĀpage"
 @{" " link "'#toc'/MAIN"}Table of Contents

 @{" " link "'#toc0'/MAIN"}Name mmuplaysmp - Play samples from modules @{" " link "'#toc1'/MAIN"}Synopsis @{"b"}mmuplaysmp@{"ub"} [@{"i"}generaloptions@{"ui"}] [@{"i"}deviceoptions@{"ui"}] [@{"i"}qualityoptions@{"ui"}] [@{"i"}otheroptions@{"ui"}] [@{"i"}MODFILE...@{"ui"}] @{" " link "'#toc2'/MAIN"}Description @{"b"}mmuplaysmp@{"ub"} is a simple sample player, it plays samples from @{"i"}MODFILE@{"ui"}s, if no @{"i"}MODFILE@{"ui"}s is given then module will be loaded from standard input. If readline support is present and module is not loaded from standard input, then playback can be controlled from the keyboard, this is the console control. When the console control is enabled @{"b"}mmuplaysmp@{"ub"} do not automatically jumps to the next sample, it waits for user input, to jump to the next sample press @{"b"}n@{"ub"} key on the keyboard. See CONSOLE CONTROL section for a list of recognized keys. if the console control is disabled and no @{"b"}-p@{"ub"} or @{"b"}--sample@{"ub"} option is given, then all samples from all @{"i"}MODFILE@{"ui"}s will be played. Samples will be played in the same order that its is found in the module. Modules will be processed in the same order that its specified at the command line. 

@{"b"}mmuplaysmp@{"ub"} is part of the MikMod Utilities package, and uses MikMod Sound Library to load and play modules. @{" " link "'#toc3'/MAIN"}Exit Status @{"b"}mmuplaysmp@{"ub"} uses standard exit status, as defined in sysexits.h. See a description of all exit codes in @{" " link "'mmu.1'/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmu@{"ub"}(1) . @{" " link "'#toc4'/MAIN"}General Options See a description of all general options in @{" " link "'mmu.1'/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmu@{"ub"}(1) . @{" " link "'#toc5'/MAIN"}Device Options @{"b"}-d, --dev=@{"ub"}@{"i"}DEVNO@{"ui"} Specify output device number which will be used for sound playback. Zero number means device autodetection, this is the default. Specify @{"b"}help@{"ub"} as argument to get a list of all possible device numbers. @{"b"}-a, --params=@{"ub"}@{"i"}PARAMS@{"ui"} Specify output device parameters. See section DRIVER PARAMETERS of libmikmod README file, to get information about all possible device parameters. @{" " link "'#toc6'/MAIN"}Quality Options @{"b"}-r, --mixfreq=@{"ub"}@{"i"}RATE@{"ui"} Sound playback frequency, in hertz. High values yield high sound quality, but need more computing power than lower values. The default value is 44100 Hz, which is compact disc quality. Other common values are 22100 Hz (radio quality), 11025 Hz (phone quality), and 8000 Hz (mu-law quality). @{"b"}-s, --stereo@{"ub"} Select stereo sound. This is the default. @{"b"}-m, --mono@{"ub"} Select mono sound. @{"b"}-1, --16bit@{"ub"} Select 16 bit sound mode. This mode yields better sound quality, but needs twice more mixing time, in comparison with 8 bit sound mode. The default is to use 16 bit sound mode. @{"b"}-8, --8bit@{"ub"} Select 8 bit sound mode. @{" " link "'#toc7'/MAIN"}Other Options @{"b"}-b, --basefreq=@{"ub"}@{"i"}RATE@{"ui"} Set the base samples frequency to @{"i"}RATE@{"ui"}. This is the default speed which will be used for playing samples. If the console control is enabled then samples can be played with speed from @{"i"}RATE@{"ui"}/2 to @{"i"}RATE@{"ui"}*2 using 0..9 keys on the keyboard. By default the base samples frequency are equivalent to the mixing frequency. @{"b"}-p, --sample=@{"ub"}@{"i"}SMPNO@{"ui"} Play only @{"i"}SMPNO@{"ui"} sample and exit. The sample number is zero based (first sample have number 0, second 1, etc). Use @{" " link "'mmuinfo.1'/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmuinfo@{"ub"}(1) to get a list of all samples in the module. If this option is given, then only one @{"i"}MODFILE@{"ui"} must be specified. If this option is not given, then all samples from all @{"i"}MODFILE@{"ui"}s will be played. @{"b"}-v, --maxvoices=@{"ub"}@{"i"}MAXV@{"ui"} Set the maximum number of voices that can by played at the same time. The default value is 2. This option has no effect if the console control is disabled. @{"b"}--nocontrol@{"ub"} Disable control from the console. @{"b"}-e, --delay=@{"ub"}@{"i"}MSEC@{"ui"} Set delay of @{"i"}MSEC@{"ui"} number of milliseconds after playing every sample. The default value is 0. This option has no effect if the console control is enabled. @{"b"}-t, --title@{"ub"} Display module title instead of file name. This option cannot be combined with the @{"b"}-q@{"ub"} option. @{"b"}-n, --samplename@{"ub"} Additionally print the sample name. This option cannot be combined with the @{"b"}-q@{"ub"} option. @{"b"}-q, --quiet@{"ub"} Do not write anything to standard output. @{"b"}-T, --filesfrom=@{"ub"}@{"i"}FILE@{"ui"} Read module list from @{"i"}FILE@{"ui"}. Each line of @{"i"}FILE@{"ui"} is a module file name. Empty lines and lines starting with # are ignored. If @{"i"}FILE@{"ui"} is -, then list will be loaded from standard input. @{"b"}-X, --filesfromcmd=@{"ub"}@{"i"}COMMAND@{"ui"} Read module list from output of @{"i"}COMMAND@{"ui"}. The @{"i"}COMMAND@{"ui"} will be passed to the shell (/bin/sh -c). Each line of output is a module file name. Empty lines and lines starting with # are ignored. @{" " link "'#toc8'/MAIN"}Console Control Console control is enabled if readline support is present (this is configured at compile-time) and module is not loaded from standard input and no @{"b"}--nocontrol@{"ub"} option is given. 

The following keys are recognized: 1..0 play sample with speed from basefreq/2 to basefreq*2 space play sample with basefreq speed s stop all playing voices n play next sample p play previous sample + increase volume - decrease volume h print kyes help q quit @{" " link "'#toc9'/MAIN"}Notes All defaults of @{"i"}quality options@{"ui"} can be changed at compile-time. To get information about compile-time configuration use @{"b"}mmu --version@{"ub"} command. @{" " link "'#toc10'/MAIN"}Bugs If you found any, please let me known. @{" " link "'#toc11'/MAIN"}Author Konstantin Korikov <lostclus@ua.fm> @{" " link "'#toc12'/MAIN"}See Also @{" " link "'mmu.guide/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmu(1) ,@{"ub"} 


